  "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/tarball/v8.126.0",
  "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/zipball/v8.126.0",
  "body": ">[!IMPORTANT]\r\n> Datadog APM now supports AWS Lambda Durable Functions. To maintain retention consistency for spans across a long-running durable execution, **create a retention filter with the retention query `operation_name:aws.durable.execute`**. Note that standard trace retention limits still apply.\r\n>\r\n> By default, the tracer creates additional checkpoints named `_datadog_{N}` to propagate trace context across function invocations. This keeps spans from multiple invocations in a single intact trace for each durable execution. To disable this behavior and treat each invocation as an individual trace, set the environment variable `DD_DURABLE_CROSS_INVOCATION_TRACING_ENABLED` to `false`.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n>[!IMPORTANT]\r\n> For Python 3.8 and 3.9: `dd-trace-py` version is [v3.19.8](https://github.com/DataDog/dd-trace-py/releases/tag/v3.19.8)\r\n> For Python >= 3.10: `dd-trace-py` version is [v4.11.0](https://github.com/DataDog/dd-trace-py/releases/tag/v4.11.0)\r\n\r\n\r\n>[!IMPORTANT]\r\n> This layer is currently unavailable in aws region `me-south-1`, due to unrelated incidents\r\n\r\n## What's Changed\r\n* ci: skip empty scenarios only on pull_request by @nccatoni in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/817\r\n* Revert \"Revert \"ci: install upstream ddtrace wheel during PR-triggered unit tests\"\" by @rithikanarayan in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/815\r\n* Revert \"Revert \"Revert \"ci: install upstream ddtrace wheel during PR-triggered unit tests\"\"\" by @brettlangdon in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/822\r\n* Revert \"Revert \"Revert \"Revert \"ci: install upstream ddtrace wheel during PR-triggered unit tests\"\"\"\" by @rithikanarayan in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/823\r\n* test: avoid side effects from mutating environ by @KowalskiThomas in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/826\r\n* Remove update_deps.yml by @pablomartinezbernardo in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/827\r\n* [SVLS-8493] feat: Rename durable span tags from aws_lambda.durable_function.* to aws.durable.* by @lym953 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/829\r\n* Add unit tests to Ci Visibility by @rithikanarayan in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/828\r\n* durable: extract trace context from checkpoints by @joeyzhao2018 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/818\r\n* fix: honor upstream trace context in Step Functions Execution.Input._datadog (APMSVLS-513) by @chemystery09 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/830\r\n* fix(deps): vuln patch: minimatch, shell-quote [tests/integration] by @gh-worker-campaigns-3e9aa4[bot] in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/832\r\n* remove private import of ddtrace functionality by @emmettbutler in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/835\r\n* remove import of private ddtrace constant by @emmettbutler in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/837\r\n* feat: inferred alb spans by @chemystery09 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/838\r\n* release v8.126.0 by @joeyzhao2018 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/841\r\n\r\n## New Contributors\r\n* @KowalskiThomas made their first contribution in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/826\r\n* @chemystery09 made their first contribution in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/830\r\n* @gh-worker-campaigns-3e9aa4[bot] made their first contribution in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/pull/832\r\n\r\n\r\n### Layers\r\n```\r\n# AWS Commercial\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python38:126\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python38-ARM:126\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python39:126\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python39-ARM:126\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python310:126\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python310-ARM:126\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python311:126\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python311-ARM:126\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python312:126\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python312-ARM:126\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python313:126\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python313-ARM:126\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python314:126\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Python314-ARM:126\r\n\r\n# AWS GovCloud \r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Python38:126\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Python38-ARM:126\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Python39:126\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Python39-ARM:126\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Python310:126\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Python310-ARM:126\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Python311:126\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Python311-ARM:126\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Python312:126\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Python312-ARM:126\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Python313:126\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Python313-ARM:126\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Python314:126\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Python314-ARM:126\r\n\r\nACCOUNT =\r\n002406178527 for us1 environment\r\n486696501492 for us2 environment\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-python/compare/v8.125.0...v8.126.0",
